Competitions.detailed-description: This competition for college and university students emphasizes the vital role of Data Structures and Algorithms (DSA). Teams of four navigate  testing their DSA, Logical Reasoning, and Object-Oriented Programming skills. The competition focuses on project development in various domains.  Recognizing top projects promotes the significance of DSA in problem-solving and creativity, offering participants a platform to showcase and enhance their skills in an ethical competitive environment.

Competitions.detailed-description: Engineer's Canvas is an inclusive competition for innovative projects and ongoing research, emphasizing Originality, technology aspects, and Purpose. Presentations focus on showcasing findings and research contributions, providing a platform for participants to demonstrate their unique perspectives in engineering and research.

Competitions.name: CTF -CODExMATH
Competitions.description: Capture The Flag (CTF) is a type of competition that challenges...
Competitions.detailedDescription: Capture The Flag (CTF) is a type of competition that challenges participants to solve a variety of security-related tasks to uncover "flags" hidden within vulnerable systems or applications. These flags are typically short strings of text that serve as proof that the participant has successfully exploited a vulnerability or solved a particular challenge.
